This filter should remove empty strings but keeps them:

```javascript
function removeEmpty(arr) {
    return arr.filter(item => !item);
}
```

Bug: The predicate `!item` keeps falsy values and removes truthy ones -- the logic is inverted.
Fix: Use `item` (truthy check) or `item !== ''` for the predicate.

```javascript
function removeEmpty(arr) {
    return arr.filter(item => item !== '');
}
```

